1
00:00:37,167 --> 00:00:40,200
<i>I won't admit to something
I didn't do.</i>

2
00:00:40,333 --> 00:00:41,267
<i> Let her be, Mom.</i>

3
00:00:41,400 --> 00:00:42,800
<i>We've already
gotten our revenge.</i>

4
00:00:42,933 --> 00:00:44,400
<i> Coleen won't do that.</i>

5
00:00:44,533 --> 00:00:45,067
<i> Yes!</i>

6
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:46,600
<i> I put laxatives!</i>

7
00:00:46,733 --> 00:00:48,167
<i> You could've killed her!</i>

8
00:00:48,300 --> 00:00:49,233
<i> You're mean!</i>

9
00:00:51,233 --> 00:00:52,133
<i> Stop it!</i>

10
00:00:52,267 --> 00:00:53,533
<i>You're really not
going to apologize?</i>

11
00:00:53,667 --> 00:00:55,367
<i>Don't you dare
test our patience.</i>

12
00:00:55,500 --> 00:00:57,000
<i>- Sorry.
- Sorry.</i>

13
00:00:57,133 --> 00:00:58,467
<i>Go ahead, pick a fight
with my daughter.</i>

14
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:01,900
<i>It'll only bring her back
to me faster, with her father.</i>

15
00:01:02,033 --> 00:01:03,267
<i>The two of them
were taken aback.</i>

16
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:04,767
<i> They ran away, didn't they?</i>

17
00:01:04,900 --> 00:01:06,800
<i>You still have the nerve
to reminisce?</i>

18
00:01:06,933 --> 00:01:08,733
<i> You monsters.</i>

19
00:01:10,100 --> 00:01:11,533
Hey, Bro.

20
00:01:11,667 --> 00:01:14,667
The blender and the air fryer
are done.

21
00:01:14,800 --> 00:01:16,833
You can come pick them up.

22
00:01:16,967 --> 00:01:18,400
I'll have the microwave
ready shortly.

23
00:01:18,533 --> 00:01:19,300
<i> All right, Bro.</i>

24
00:01:19,433 --> 00:01:20,667
<i> I'll drop by tomorrow.</i>

25
00:01:20,800 --> 00:01:23,100
<i>I've got three more things
to bring in for repair anyway.</i>

26
00:01:23,233 --> 00:01:24,233
There we go!

27
00:01:24,367 --> 00:01:25,933
All right, all right.
Thanks, Bro.

28
00:01:26,067 --> 00:01:27,233
Okay then, see you.

29
00:01:29,033 --> 00:01:30,067
Manuel?

30
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:31,200
Manuel!

31
00:01:31,333 --> 00:01:34,500
Jeff is coming back to FMP!

32
00:01:34,633 --> 00:01:38,333
Thank God you and our eldest
have finally made peace.

33
00:01:47,533 --> 00:01:49,300
Your eldest, I mean.

34
00:01:49,433 --> 00:01:51,567
Jeffrey.

35
00:01:56,933 --> 00:01:57,967
Yeah.

36
00:02:00,100 --> 00:02:01,833
Just a little more.

37
00:02:01,967 --> 00:02:03,300
You're next.

38
00:02:04,500 --> 00:02:06,800
You'll make peace
with him, too.

39
00:02:06,933 --> 00:02:08,100
I really hope so.

40
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:13,600
And I hope Andrea
comes around, too.

41
00:02:35,667 --> 00:02:37,467
Andrea, talk to me. Please.

42
00:02:38,867 --> 00:02:39,600
Well, of course.

43
00:02:41,067 --> 00:02:43,233
Mom paid off all your debts.

44
00:02:43,367 --> 00:02:46,367
So naturally,
you went back to her.

45
00:02:50,267 --> 00:02:51,033
Andrea, I'm drowning here.

46
00:02:51,167 --> 00:02:52,300
What am I supposed to do?

47
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:55,433
Is it really so wrong
to swallow my pride?

48
00:02:55,567 --> 00:02:56,900
She's our mother, after all.

49
00:02:59,900 --> 00:03:01,900
So, what's next?

50
00:03:02,033 --> 00:03:03,133
Are you moving back home, too?

51
00:03:03,267 --> 00:03:05,067
No.

52
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:06,733
I'm not going back there as long
as your father

53
00:03:06,867 --> 00:03:09,767
and his child are still living
in that house.

54
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:11,267
I have my own family now,
my own home.

55
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:13,833
Why would I go back?

56
00:03:13,967 --> 00:03:14,667
Good.

57
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:18,633
At least we still have
one thing in common.

58
00:03:21,333 --> 00:03:24,533
I thought you were ready
to fold even to your father.

59
00:03:24,667 --> 00:03:26,300
He's not part of this.

60
00:03:28,167 --> 00:03:31,267
It's only about mom.

61
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:33,500
Don't drag her into
your anger at dad.

62
00:03:35,533 --> 00:03:36,867
I'm trying, Jeff.

63
00:03:38,567 --> 00:03:40,000
I really am.

64
00:03:42,533 --> 00:03:46,933
Every time I remember
that mom chose that man over us,

65
00:03:47,067 --> 00:03:48,900
it feels like
my heart's being stabbed.

66
00:03:50,933 --> 00:03:52,900
It still hurts.

67
00:03:55,033 --> 00:03:56,300
Well, keep trying then.

68
00:03:59,833 --> 00:04:01,333
I know you miss mom.

69
00:04:03,467 --> 00:04:04,933
You worry about her.

70
00:04:08,833 --> 00:04:10,000
Didn't you even go check on her

71
00:04:10,133 --> 00:04:12,533
when City Sanitation shut down
the FMP?

72
00:04:15,300 --> 00:04:16,233
You checked on her.

73
00:04:19,700 --> 00:04:21,133
I was there. I saw you.

74
00:04:23,967 --> 00:04:25,133
<i> Hello, Attorney.</i>

75
00:04:25,267 --> 00:04:27,900
<i>The closure order
has been served.</i>

76
00:04:28,067 --> 00:04:30,400
<i> Yes. We'll meet at City Hall.</i>

77
00:04:30,533 --> 00:04:32,233
<i> Thank you very much, Attorney.</i>

78
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:38,867
I miss her so much, Jeff.

79
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:44,400
You just don't know.

80
00:04:46,067 --> 00:04:47,900
I miss Mom terribly.

81
00:04:51,367 --> 00:04:52,533
So that's it.

82
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:57,533
Why won't you make
peace with her?

83
00:04:57,667 --> 00:04:58,933
Just ignore your father.

84
00:05:00,700 --> 00:05:02,067
No.

85
00:05:02,233 --> 00:05:03,900
As long as she's with her ex...

86
00:05:05,933 --> 00:05:07,667
I'm not going back
to that house.

87
00:05:11,367 --> 00:05:13,367
Sometimes I even think,

88
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:15,967
maybe it's better if Mom
just gets hurt again.

89
00:05:16,100 --> 00:05:17,333
Andrea, what are you saying?

90
00:05:17,467 --> 00:05:18,867
I know it's wrong, Jeff.

91
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:23,400
But if that's the only way
for her

92
00:05:23,533 --> 00:05:26,133
to finally let go of your
father,

93
00:05:26,267 --> 00:05:28,667
so we can all be together
again...

94
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:30,467
Me, Mom, you, and Coleen.

95
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:31,567
That's all I want.

96
00:05:48,900 --> 00:05:52,067
Dad, I'm really excited
about your return to FMP.

97
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:54,467
- I'm sure Mom's excited too.
- Hey, don't say anything yet.

98
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:55,700
I haven't told her.

99
00:05:55,833 --> 00:05:56,833
It's a surprise.

100
00:06:00,367 --> 00:06:01,967
You're leaving already?

101
00:06:02,100 --> 00:06:03,000
Yeah.

102
00:06:03,133 --> 00:06:05,600
My team leader let me
start earlier again.

103
00:06:07,733 --> 00:06:10,667
Daisy, you've been doing
that a lot lately.

104
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:14,300
You know, you don't even
have to work overtime anymore.

105
00:06:14,433 --> 00:06:16,500
Because I'm back at FMP.

106
00:06:16,633 --> 00:06:19,467
That's my surprise for you!

107
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:20,967
Good.

108
00:06:21,100 --> 00:06:23,200
I've been telling you that
for a long time.

109
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:27,167
All right, I'll get going.

110
00:06:27,300 --> 00:06:28,100
Bye, Mom.

111
00:06:28,233 --> 00:06:29,900
Sorry, I didn't
get to cook dinner.

112
00:06:30,033 --> 00:06:33,600
You'll have to take care
of your dinner, okay?

113
00:06:33,733 --> 00:06:34,567
I'll go ahead, Sweetie.

114
00:06:34,700 --> 00:06:35,367
Bye, Mom.

115
00:06:45,267 --> 00:06:45,833
Dear.

116
00:06:45,967 --> 00:06:46,867
Yes?

117
00:06:48,067 --> 00:06:49,900
Is your mom angry at me?

118
00:06:50,033 --> 00:06:52,300
She's been avoiding me
for days now.

119
00:06:52,433 --> 00:06:54,600
I don't think so, Dad.

120
00:06:54,733 --> 00:06:56,033
Mom's just been really busy.

121
00:06:59,067 --> 00:07:00,333
Oh, Dad!

122
00:07:00,467 --> 00:07:01,800
I forgot something!

123
00:07:01,933 --> 00:07:02,900
What is it?

124
00:07:03,033 --> 00:07:06,300
Have I told you "I love you"
today?

125
00:07:06,433 --> 00:07:08,300
Tetay, I thought
something had happened!

126
00:07:08,433 --> 00:07:09,433
Yes, earlier.

127
00:07:09,567 --> 00:07:11,467
That was the first thing
you did when you woke up.

128
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:14,233
I didn't forget after all,
but I'm making up for it anyway.

129
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:15,667
I love you, Dad!

130
00:07:20,700 --> 00:07:21,633
Is this your favorite?

131
00:07:21,767 --> 00:07:23,267
- Yes, it is.
- Yeah. It's your favorite.

132
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:27,433
There you go.

133
00:07:36,867 --> 00:07:37,833
Wait.

134
00:07:43,967 --> 00:07:46,233
- Hey.
- Can I have some cooking oil?

135
00:07:46,367 --> 00:07:47,400
I ran out.

136
00:07:47,567 --> 00:07:48,333
It's raining outside.

137
00:07:48,467 --> 00:07:49,633
I'm feeling lazy.

138
00:07:49,767 --> 00:07:50,900
Cooking oil?

139
00:07:51,033 --> 00:07:52,000
I don't have any oil.

140
00:07:52,133 --> 00:07:53,000
You frying again?

141
00:07:53,133 --> 00:07:55,167
You know, you always
eat unhealthy food.

142
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:56,933
Better yet,
why don't you join me?

143
00:07:57,067 --> 00:07:58,367
I made some tamarind
chicken soup.

144
00:07:58,500 --> 00:07:59,200
Come on.

145
00:07:59,333 --> 00:08:00,167
This one's yours.

146
00:08:00,300 --> 00:08:00,900
Oh, please.

147
00:08:01,033 --> 00:08:01,833
Have a seat.

148
00:08:05,267 --> 00:08:07,133
You know how to cook?

149
00:08:07,267 --> 00:08:08,333
Yes.

150
00:08:08,467 --> 00:08:10,100
I spent a lot of time
in the kitchen back then.

151
00:08:10,233 --> 00:08:11,667
I was grandmother's
assistant cook.

152
00:08:15,467 --> 00:08:17,533
Me too, but with mom.

153
00:08:17,667 --> 00:08:19,900
But I never really
learned to cook.

154
00:08:20,033 --> 00:08:22,533
I was just an assistant, really.

155
00:08:22,700 --> 00:08:23,500
What a shame.

156
00:08:23,633 --> 00:08:25,333
I wish you had
learned her recipes.

157
00:08:27,733 --> 00:08:29,867
- Try this.
- Thank you.

158
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:32,800
More soup...

159
00:08:32,933 --> 00:08:35,200
Looks delicious.

160
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:37,833
Veggies, and of course...

161
00:08:37,967 --> 00:08:39,500
Hey, that's a lot!

162
00:08:39,633 --> 00:08:41,133
It's really good.

163
00:08:41,267 --> 00:08:42,433
That's enough!

164
00:08:42,567 --> 00:08:43,167
Okay, fine.

165
00:08:43,300 --> 00:08:44,567
This is mine, this is mine.

166
00:08:47,633 --> 00:08:50,100
Okay. Let's try this.

167
00:09:00,300 --> 00:09:01,100
Delicious.

168
00:09:01,233 --> 00:09:02,800
Delicious, isn't it?
Well, of course!

169
00:09:02,933 --> 00:09:04,233
It's home-cooked.

170
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:15,667
What's that?

171
00:09:17,067 --> 00:09:19,800
Is it so good that it's
making you close your eyes?

172
00:09:19,933 --> 00:09:23,367
It's just like
mom's cooking.

173
00:09:25,100 --> 00:09:27,500
I really miss it.

174
00:09:27,667 --> 00:09:29,533
The cooking?

175
00:09:29,667 --> 00:09:30,800
Or your mom?

176
00:09:50,933 --> 00:09:52,233
Oh, why are you still awake?

177
00:09:55,233 --> 00:09:56,633
I'm just waiting
for sleep to come.

178
00:10:02,033 --> 00:10:06,433
Sir Manuel,
here's your hot coffee.

179
00:10:06,567 --> 00:10:08,533
As hot as you.

180
00:10:08,667 --> 00:10:10,500
You're so silly, Didang.

181
00:10:10,633 --> 00:10:11,433
Thank you.

182
00:10:12,967 --> 00:10:14,867
Didang, can you please
make another cup?

183
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:17,967
Give that to Felma first.

184
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:20,167
No, no, it's okay.

185
00:10:20,300 --> 00:10:21,667
Come on, join me.

186
00:10:23,133 --> 00:10:24,267
Yes, Ma'am.

187
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:28,500
Coffee tastes better with
a weather like this, right?

188
00:10:28,633 --> 00:10:30,233
I'll make you a cup.

189
00:10:33,333 --> 00:10:36,600
How's FMP?

190
00:10:36,767 --> 00:10:41,067
Is there any result from
the CPHSO investigation?

191
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:42,367
Yes.

192
00:10:44,367 --> 00:10:47,400
We're just waiting
for the decision.

193
00:10:47,533 --> 00:10:50,667
And what about Hazel's lawsuit?

194
00:10:51,867 --> 00:10:55,400
I'll talk to Attorney Yeban
tomorrow.

195
00:10:58,900 --> 00:11:01,167
Felma, you look restless.

196
00:11:02,900 --> 00:11:04,067
Is there a problem?

197
00:11:09,767 --> 00:11:10,600
Nothing.

198
00:11:12,967 --> 00:11:15,667
I'm already sleepy.

199
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:16,633
Go to bed, too.

200
00:11:16,767 --> 00:11:20,000
Sir Manuel,
here's your hot coffee.

201
00:11:23,400 --> 00:11:24,500
Didang!

202
00:11:24,633 --> 00:11:26,167
- Sorry, Sir.
- Why are you being careless?

203
00:11:26,300 --> 00:11:28,233
- It's okay.
- Didang, get a towel.

204
00:11:28,367 --> 00:11:29,167
Oh, no.

205
00:11:29,300 --> 00:11:31,367
- It's okay.
- Manuel!

206
00:11:31,500 --> 00:11:33,067
- Go on...
- Wait, are you hurt?

207
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:35,000
No, I'm okay.

208
00:11:35,133 --> 00:11:35,933
Did you get burned?

209
00:11:36,067 --> 00:11:36,867
No.

210
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:37,800
Felma...

211
00:11:37,933 --> 00:11:38,867
- Ma'am...
- Oh, no!

212
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:41,267
I can't feel my leg anymore,
remember?

213
00:11:41,433 --> 00:11:42,233
Let me.

214
00:11:42,367 --> 00:11:43,667
Come on, it's okay.

215
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:46,433
But still.

216
00:11:46,567 --> 00:11:49,433
Your skin can still get burned.

217
00:11:49,567 --> 00:11:51,033
I'll just wipe this off, okay?

218
00:11:51,167 --> 00:11:52,233
Then you should change
your clothes.

219
00:11:52,367 --> 00:11:57,433
Sir Manuel, we know you
can't feel your leg anymore.

220
00:11:57,567 --> 00:11:59,167
But what about your heart?

221
00:12:01,900 --> 00:12:03,233
Didang!

222
00:12:03,367 --> 00:12:05,000
What's wrong with you?

223
00:12:05,133 --> 00:12:06,000
Oh, wow!

224
00:12:06,133 --> 00:12:07,767
You actually heard that?

225
00:12:07,900 --> 00:12:09,067
I whispered it.

226
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:10,800
You've got such sharp ears,
Ma'am.

227
00:12:11,933 --> 00:12:14,100
I'll tidy these coffees up now.

228
00:12:29,100 --> 00:12:30,600
According to Atty. Yeban,

229
00:12:30,733 --> 00:12:34,967
these are the cases I can file
against Hazel.

230
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:38,500
Reckless imprudence resulting
in physical injuries,

231
00:12:38,633 --> 00:12:41,200
administering injurious
substances,

232
00:12:41,333 --> 00:12:45,367
and moral and actual exemplary
damages.

233
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:46,567
That's a lot, right?

234
00:12:46,700 --> 00:12:47,700
Right?

235
00:12:47,867 --> 00:12:50,333
Go! Sue those two evil little
gremlins already!

236
00:12:50,467 --> 00:12:53,067
The problem is, we don't
have solid evidence

237
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:57,367
against Hazel
and her accomplices...

238
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:59,767
that they were the ones who
actually put the laxatives

239
00:12:59,900 --> 00:13:01,933
in the<i> sisig</i> .

240
00:13:02,067 --> 00:13:05,933
Unless she confesses.

241
00:13:06,067 --> 00:13:07,467
You all know it's impossible
for her to do that, Mom.

242
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:08,367
She would never do
something like that.

243
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:10,033
You're right, Son.

244
00:13:10,167 --> 00:13:16,733
We'll just be wasting our time
trying to find evidence.

245
00:13:16,867 --> 00:13:18,267
Let's set it aside for now.

246
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:24,833
What matters is we've confirmed
it was sabotage.

247
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:27,867
FMP did nothing wrong.

248
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:32,433
Let's just focus on getting
operations back up and running.

249
00:13:32,567 --> 00:13:34,500
But, when?

250
00:13:34,633 --> 00:13:38,500
Every day, our financial status
is in crisis.

251
00:13:38,633 --> 00:13:42,367
Every day we don't open,
our funds keep draining.

252
00:13:42,500 --> 00:13:46,900
And it's not just a small hole,
it's a huge one.

253
00:13:47,033 --> 00:13:48,967
Look at this.

254
00:13:53,867 --> 00:13:56,800
Oh, it's the Chief Sanitation
Officer from the CPHSO.

255
00:13:56,967 --> 00:13:58,067
Hold on.

256
00:14:00,267 --> 00:14:01,400
Hello?

257
00:14:01,533 --> 00:14:02,767
Mr. Roldan?

258
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:08,300
Thank you, Sir.

259
00:14:14,167 --> 00:14:16,167
Their investigation is done.

260
00:14:20,100 --> 00:14:23,667
FMP has no violations!

261
00:14:23,800 --> 00:14:25,133
Amazing!

262
00:14:25,267 --> 00:14:27,900
All the areas they
inspected were clean.

263
00:14:28,067 --> 00:14:31,167
And the product sample we sent?

264
00:14:31,300 --> 00:14:32,167
All clean.

265
00:14:32,300 --> 00:14:33,533
No issues at all.

266
00:14:33,667 --> 00:14:34,267
Yes!

267
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:35,867
Even in the lab tests, so...

268
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,200
We're cleared!

269
00:14:38,933 --> 00:14:40,367
- You should celebrate!
- Congratulations!

270
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:45,133
- Where do we go, Son?
- Nice!

271
00:14:45,267 --> 00:14:46,567
No more. This won't bleed
any further.

272
00:14:46,700 --> 00:14:47,700
It's over. It's done.

273
00:14:47,833 --> 00:14:48,800
The money will start
flowing again.

274
00:14:48,933 --> 00:14:49,233
We've patched the hole.
Covered it up, sealed it!

275
00:14:49,367 --> 00:14:50,367
Yes!

276
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:52,400
Thank you, Lord!

277
00:15:02,767 --> 00:15:04,633
Yes, to all our FMP family
and supporters...

278
00:15:04,767 --> 00:15:08,300
We've proven that the
factory's facility

279
00:15:08,433 --> 00:15:10,400
is clean and safe.

280
00:15:10,533 --> 00:15:14,100
There was no contamination
or spoilage in our products,

281
00:15:14,233 --> 00:15:17,667
so we did not violate
any standards.

282
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:21,033
What about the alleged
food poisoning incident

283
00:15:21,167 --> 00:15:22,967
at Luntian Park?

284
00:15:23,100 --> 00:15:25,600
It was an isolated case.

285
00:15:25,733 --> 00:15:28,667
Someone sabotaged FMP.

286
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:30,100
That's a separate matter,

287
00:15:30,233 --> 00:15:32,333
and we're currently
investigating it.

288
00:15:32,467 --> 00:15:33,733
Thank you very much.

289
00:15:33,867 --> 00:15:35,167
Thank you, as well.

290
00:15:40,833 --> 00:15:42,633
They're back in business.

291
00:15:44,567 --> 00:15:45,867
Yes.

292
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:49,233
But I'm sure they lost a fortune
during the closure.

293
00:15:49,367 --> 00:15:53,633
And trust me, Alice, some of
their customers will be scared

294
00:15:53,767 --> 00:15:55,900
to eat FMP products anyway.

295
00:15:56,033 --> 00:15:58,433
So, I still win.

296
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:06,600
And I will win the new battle
I just started.

297
00:16:06,733 --> 00:16:07,767
Remember?

298
00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:09,733
The spy cameras?

299
00:16:09,900 --> 00:16:10,433
Yes, yes.

300
00:16:10,567 --> 00:16:12,300
What about it?

301
00:16:12,433 --> 00:16:16,033
Well, I'm not planting
spy cameras just to gossip.

302
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:21,967
I'm gathering evidence
for the case I'm filing

303
00:16:22,100 --> 00:16:25,000
against Manuel
and that flirty Felma.

304
00:16:25,133 --> 00:16:27,200
Concubinage.

305
00:16:27,333 --> 00:16:28,867
You're really going
to have Manuel arrested?

306
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:30,333
You think you can?

307
00:16:30,467 --> 00:16:31,733
Yes.

308
00:16:34,167 --> 00:16:37,933
Better that than him ending up
with that flirty Felma.

309
00:16:38,067 --> 00:16:39,833
Wait, friend.

310
00:16:39,967 --> 00:16:43,300
You know illegally obtained
videos

311
00:16:43,467 --> 00:16:45,733
are inadmissible in court,
right?

312
00:16:45,867 --> 00:16:47,067
Of course.

313
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:49,600
I thought of that.

314
00:16:49,733 --> 00:16:55,400
But I also thought I might
still find other evidence.

315
00:16:55,533 --> 00:16:57,767
I can use those against them.

316
00:17:00,067 --> 00:17:03,700
Those videos will
cause a scandal.

317
00:17:04,633 --> 00:17:06,833
If the courts fail me,

318
00:17:08,267 --> 00:17:11,133
I'll use the court
of public opinion.

319
00:17:11,267 --> 00:17:12,800
Trial by publicity.

320
00:17:12,933 --> 00:17:14,633
And Felma?

321
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:18,000
I'll expose her to the world
of extra-marital affairs.

322
00:17:37,967 --> 00:17:40,700
We can now eat.

323
00:17:40,833 --> 00:17:42,500
Let's enjoy ourselves, okay?

324
00:17:42,633 --> 00:17:45,733
We deserve it,
but let's not get wasted!

325
00:17:45,867 --> 00:17:47,133
Mommy Pretty!

326
00:17:47,267 --> 00:17:48,267
Tetay!

327
00:17:48,433 --> 00:17:49,400
Tetay!

328
00:17:49,533 --> 00:17:50,900
I missed you.

329
00:17:51,033 --> 00:17:51,900
I missed you, too.

330
00:17:52,033 --> 00:17:52,667
- Mom.
- Son.

331
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:53,700
Thank you for coming.

332
00:17:53,833 --> 00:17:56,300
Of course.

333
00:17:56,433 --> 00:17:57,433
Where's Daisy?

334
00:17:57,567 --> 00:18:00,367
Well, Mom, I asked her
to take a leave,

335
00:18:00,500 --> 00:18:01,667
but she wouldn't.

336
00:18:01,800 --> 00:18:03,267
Son, is there something wrong?

337
00:18:05,267 --> 00:18:06,467
Not exactly, Mom...

338
00:18:08,700 --> 00:18:10,200
but it feels like there is.

339
00:18:10,333 --> 00:18:12,867
You two need to talk it out.

340
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,233
Yes, Mom.

341
00:18:16,733 --> 00:18:18,433
Your sister?

342
00:18:18,567 --> 00:18:19,933
Andrea says she's busy
with work, Mom.

343
00:18:20,067 --> 00:18:21,267
<i>- Mom.
- She has so much going on.</i>

344
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:22,767
Mom, try this barbecue.

345
00:18:22,933 --> 00:18:24,900
You'll like the seasoning...

346
00:18:35,967 --> 00:18:37,933
Can you really ignore me?

347
00:18:38,067 --> 00:18:41,100
I can't.

348
00:18:41,233 --> 00:18:42,400
Come here.

349
00:18:48,233 --> 00:18:49,867
You're trying to ignore me.

350
00:18:52,733 --> 00:18:53,667
No!

351
00:18:57,600 --> 00:18:58,567
Stop crying.

352
00:18:58,700 --> 00:19:00,200
We should be celebrating.

353
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:02,367
You've got lots of barbecue.

354
00:19:02,500 --> 00:19:04,000
The other one's for mom.

355
00:19:04,133 --> 00:19:05,700
There's still a lot.

356
00:19:05,833 --> 00:19:07,900
Of course, it's for later.

357
00:19:08,033 --> 00:19:10,467
-For mom? But you're holding it.
-And for Tetay.

358
00:19:10,600 --> 00:19:12,367
You didn't even know
we were here.

359
00:19:18,033 --> 00:19:20,433
You eat a lot!

360
00:19:20,567 --> 00:19:21,367
Looks like someone's drunk.

361
00:19:21,500 --> 00:19:22,567
Mom, look. He's getting drunk!

362
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:24,400
Too much drinking is not
allowed!

363
00:19:26,233 --> 00:19:27,233
Enjoy.

364
00:19:27,367 --> 00:19:28,733
- I'll just fix the water.
- Go ahead, Son.

365
00:19:31,467 --> 00:19:32,967
Who's starting the karaoke?

366
00:19:33,100 --> 00:19:33,800
There's a prize!

367
00:19:33,933 --> 00:19:34,800
A prize?

368
00:19:37,833 --> 00:19:38,800
Yes, you should all join.

369
00:19:38,933 --> 00:19:40,200
I'll join.

370
00:19:40,333 --> 00:19:42,300
Do you want to join, Tetay?

371
00:19:42,433 --> 00:19:43,167
Father will sing.

372
00:19:43,300 --> 00:19:45,200
Jeff will sing.

373
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:55,533
Jeff, here's some afritada.

374
00:19:55,667 --> 00:19:58,367
I removed the fat and
added lots of potatoes.

375
00:19:58,500 --> 00:19:59,800
Isn't that how you like it?

376
00:20:11,033 --> 00:20:12,567
Jeff, please.

377
00:20:12,700 --> 00:20:13,900
Talk to me.

378
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:18,400
<i> Dad!</i>

379
00:20:18,533 --> 00:20:19,500
<i> Join us, please.</i>

380
00:20:19,633 --> 00:20:21,367
<i>Hide-and-seek. But you're "it".</i>

381
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:23,000
<i>You're letting me join,
but I'm the one who's "it"?</i>

382
00:20:23,133 --> 00:20:23,900
<i> Yes!</i>

383
00:20:24,033 --> 00:20:24,833
<i> That's unfair.</i>

384
00:20:24,967 --> 00:20:25,833
<i> Come on!</i>

385
00:20:25,967 --> 00:20:27,400
<i>- Let's go, Dad!
- Okay, okay, okay.</i>

386
00:20:27,533 --> 00:20:28,500
<i> Fine.</i>

387
00:20:28,633 --> 00:20:31,533
<i>Hide and seek,
under the moon so bright...</i>

388
00:20:31,667 --> 00:20:32,833
<i> When I count to ten...</i>

389
00:20:32,967 --> 00:20:34,667
<i> Dad, you're so good!</i>

390
00:20:36,167 --> 00:20:37,500
<i> No, that's not counted!</i>

391
00:20:37,633 --> 00:20:38,800
<i> No.</i>

392
00:20:38,933 --> 00:20:39,800
<i> There's no score!</i>

393
00:20:47,067 --> 00:20:48,133
<i> That's good, son!</i>

394
00:20:50,100 --> 00:20:51,833
<i>Miss, can I buy some ensaymada?</i>

395
00:20:53,633 --> 00:20:54,767
<i> Three, please.</i>

396
00:20:54,900 --> 00:20:56,133
<i> One each for you, okay?</i>

397
00:20:56,267 --> 00:20:58,500
<i>And the other one's
for your mom.</i>

398
00:20:58,633 --> 00:21:00,733
<i>Baby Coleen can't
have one yet anyway.</i>

399
00:21:00,867 --> 00:21:02,467
<i> But what about you, Dad?</i>

400
00:21:02,600 --> 00:21:03,733
<i> No need. Don't worry about me.</i>

401
00:21:03,867 --> 00:21:07,033
<i>As long as I see you all
well-fed, I'm already happy.</i>

402
00:21:07,167 --> 00:21:09,033
<i> Dad is so sweet.</i>

403
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:11,067
<i> Thank you, Dad.</i>

404
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:14,133
<i>Jeffrey, you'll be your
mother's partner now.</i>

405
00:21:14,267 --> 00:21:16,033
<i> And your siblings', too.</i>

406
00:21:16,167 --> 00:21:17,100
<i>Take good care of them,
all right?</i>

407
00:21:17,233 --> 00:21:18,667
<i> Do you understand?</i>

408
00:21:18,800 --> 00:21:20,933
<i> Yes, Dad.</i>

409
00:21:21,067 --> 00:21:22,233
<i> Is it true?</i>

410
00:21:22,367 --> 00:21:23,600
<i> What is?</i>

411
00:21:23,733 --> 00:21:25,900
<i> That dad has another child?</i>

412
00:21:27,933 --> 00:21:29,667
<i> Yes, my dear children.</i>

413
00:21:29,800 --> 00:21:30,533
<i> You're the wife.</i>

414
00:21:30,667 --> 00:21:33,567
<i> Take him back from Hazel.</i>

415
00:21:33,700 --> 00:21:34,800
<i> Yes, Mom.</i>

416
00:21:34,933 --> 00:21:36,900
<i> Please take Dad back.</i>

417
00:21:37,033 --> 00:21:39,000
<i> I can't do that, dear.</i>

418
00:21:39,133 --> 00:21:41,300
<i>He's already married
to that woman.</i>

419
00:21:41,433 --> 00:21:43,733
<i>Why did you marry someone else?</i>

420
00:21:43,900 --> 00:21:45,567
<i>Why did you have
a child with her?</i>

421
00:21:45,700 --> 00:21:47,900
<i> Dear, it's hard to explain.</i>

422
00:21:48,033 --> 00:21:49,667
<i> Give it to me!</i>

423
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:51,467
<i> Manuel, please!</i>

424
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:53,633
<i>Don't make things harder
for your child!</i>

425
00:21:53,767 --> 00:21:55,233
<i> Give it to me!</i>

426
00:21:55,367 --> 00:21:56,000
<i> Jeff, what are you doing?</i>

427
00:21:56,133 --> 00:21:57,367
<i> I'll do my best to get home.</i>

428
00:21:57,500 --> 00:21:59,467
<i> Stop making promises!</i>

429
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:03,067
<i>And stop calling us from now on!</i>

430
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:04,167
<i> Jeffrey! Come on!</i>

431
00:22:04,300 --> 00:22:06,100
<i>You don't love us anymore,
right?</i>

432
00:22:06,233 --> 00:22:07,333
<i> Hello, Jeffrey!</i>

433
00:22:07,467 --> 00:22:08,833
<i> Stay with your new family!</i>

434
00:22:08,967 --> 00:22:11,233
<i> Jeff!</i>

435
00:22:11,367 --> 00:22:12,933
Son, I'm begging you.

436
00:22:15,667 --> 00:22:17,500
- Son!
- I said let go of me!

437
00:22:28,467 --> 00:22:29,533
Please excuse me.

438
00:22:29,667 --> 00:22:30,500
I'll be right back.

439
00:22:33,333 --> 00:22:34,167
Just keep on eating.

440
00:22:38,667 --> 00:22:39,467
Jeff!

441
00:22:39,600 --> 00:22:40,133
Jeff!

442
00:22:40,267 --> 00:22:41,833
Felma, let me do it.

443
00:22:41,967 --> 00:22:43,433
Go on, I'll take care of him.

444
00:23:01,133 --> 00:23:03,800
You're so stubborn!

445
00:23:03,933 --> 00:23:05,100
What do I have to do
to make you understand

446
00:23:05,233 --> 00:23:07,167
that I don't want to talk
to you?

447
00:23:10,167 --> 00:23:12,567
And me?

448
00:23:12,700 --> 00:23:15,367
What do I have to do
so you'll listen to me?

449
00:23:17,900 --> 00:23:20,400
Jeff, son, just one minute.

450
00:23:23,233 --> 00:23:26,200
My son, I'm humbling myself.

451
00:23:29,967 --> 00:23:32,033
I'm begging you, Son.

452
00:23:32,167 --> 00:23:34,000
I'm already begging
for your forgiveness.

453
00:23:34,133 --> 00:23:36,133
What else do you want me to do?

454
00:23:36,267 --> 00:23:37,033
What else?

455
00:23:40,633 --> 00:23:42,433
You want one minute?

456
00:23:42,567 --> 00:23:44,000
Fine. I'll give it to you.

457
00:23:44,133 --> 00:23:45,767
I'll time it.

458
00:23:45,900 --> 00:23:47,400
One minute. I'll listen.

459
00:23:50,133 --> 00:23:52,700
Can't we talk without
you getting angry?

460
00:23:54,367 --> 00:23:55,067
That's five seconds already.

461
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:56,733
Don't waste
your one minute.

462
00:24:00,067 --> 00:24:01,000
Time is ticking.

463
00:24:03,867 --> 00:24:05,067
Why did you go quiet?

464
00:24:08,700 --> 00:24:09,967
Don't even try to interfere.

465
00:24:11,633 --> 00:24:13,567
Why not?

466
00:24:13,700 --> 00:24:15,200
This is family business.

467
00:24:15,333 --> 00:24:16,667
You're not part of it.

468
00:24:38,367 --> 00:24:39,733
I love you, Son.

469
00:24:42,367 --> 00:24:43,167
If you love me...

470
00:24:46,267 --> 00:24:47,600
Then why did you leave me?

471
00:24:51,067 --> 00:24:55,767
And if you really love me,
you'd know my favorite dish.

472
00:24:55,900 --> 00:24:57,100
It's<i> laing</i> .

473
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:01,833
The one you cook for me

474
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,400
because you know
it's what I like.

475
00:25:07,100 --> 00:25:09,467
Andrea's the one
who loves mom's afritada.

476
00:25:28,833 --> 00:25:32,100
Please be patient with dad.

477
00:25:32,233 --> 00:25:34,267
He's still hurting.

478
00:25:35,833 --> 00:25:39,100
But please, don't be
angry at him, okay?

479
00:25:55,567 --> 00:25:57,833
You're not even part
of this family!

480
00:25:57,967 --> 00:26:00,967
Good thing I never became part
of your family.

481
00:26:01,100 --> 00:26:02,967
Because I don't want siblings

482
00:26:03,100 --> 00:26:05,000
who are rude and don't know
how to forgive.

483
00:26:06,833 --> 00:26:08,200
Hey! That's enough!

484
00:26:08,333 --> 00:26:11,133
- Stop!
- Aren't you tired of fighting?

485
00:26:11,300 --> 00:26:13,200
We're family, aren't we?

486
00:26:13,333 --> 00:26:16,333
We should be listening
to each other.

487
00:26:16,467 --> 00:26:17,767
Dad, I don't want this anymore.

488
00:26:17,900 --> 00:26:21,533
The reason we stayed away from
mommy is that she's hurting us.

489
00:26:21,667 --> 00:26:22,933
Dad, I don't want
to be here anymore.

490
00:26:23,067 --> 00:26:24,567
Let's just leave.

491
00:26:24,700 --> 00:26:25,800
Please.
